1
00:00:54,800 --> 00:00:55,600
Please.

2
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:34,410
Where are you touching?

3
00:01:42,640 --> 00:01:43,970
Where are you touching?

4
00:01:44,759 --> 00:01:45,289
Get down.

5
00:01:46,759 --> 00:01:48,240
You don't even know him,

6
00:01:49,080 --> 00:01:51,200
and you dare to glare at him?

7
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:55,039
This is the famous Officer Shao.

8
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,200
Officer Shao.

9
00:01:59,039 --> 00:02:01,280
What brings you here?

10
00:02:01,720 --> 00:02:02,520
Do you know me?

11
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:06,480
You really have a short memory.

12
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:07,920
Let me remind you.

13
00:02:08,520 --> 00:02:10,320
The incident at Boss Bar years ago,

14
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:13,400
when you personally arrested my boss,

15
00:02:13,400 --> 00:02:15,360
I remember it vividly.

16
00:02:17,160 --> 00:02:18,800
Your boss is Sang Rong.

17
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:21,760
Looking for revenge?

18
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,760
To be honest, I've thought about it.

19
00:02:26,560 --> 00:02:28,090
And technically speaking,

20
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,760
he's my brother-in-law.

21
00:02:29,760 --> 00:02:31,820
Brother Rong treated me really well.

22
00:02:34,040 --> 00:02:35,320
But as for this matter,

23
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,280
let's not mention it for now.

24
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,040
Are you here for a case,

25
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,920
or just to play a few rounds?

26
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,600
I'm no longer a cop.

27
00:02:44,600 --> 00:02:46,680
Don't call me Officer Shao.

28
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:49,020
I just want to play a few rounds today.

29
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:50,840
As for our past grudges,

30
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:52,720
can we put them aside for now?

31
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:53,760
Put them aside.

32
00:02:53,760 --> 00:02:54,720
Definitely.

33
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:56,000
I'm running a business here.

34
00:02:56,000 --> 00:02:57,200
Harmony brings wealth.

35
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:57,640
Here,

36
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,520
it's ready for you.

37
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,520
But Officer Shao,

38
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,160
I must remind you

39
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:09,360
that gambling is risky.

40
00:03:09,880 --> 00:03:11,720
Since you're not a cop anymore,

41
00:03:11,720 --> 00:03:13,760
won't you lose all your savings

42
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,240
in just a few rounds?

43
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,440
Don't wait until you lose everything,

44
00:03:17,440 --> 00:03:18,720
and have to walk back.

45
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:21,400
Yes, you have a point.

46
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:24,079
Maybe I should keep 3,000 for gas.

47
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:28,440
You haven't even started playing yet,

48
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,840
and you're already thinking about losing.

49
00:03:31,880 --> 00:03:33,120
It's fine.

50
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:34,960
Officer Shao.

51
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:37,640
Even if you lose,

52
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:39,120
I've got your back.

53
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:42,360
But this girl has a nice figure,

54
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,560
and a pretty face.

55
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,400
Can she spend the night with me?

56
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,800
I'll count it as 100,000.

57
00:03:51,120 --> 00:03:53,850
Why don't you win all this money first? All right?

58
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:56,240
Are you done catching up?

59
00:03:56,240 --> 00:03:57,440
Are we playing or not?

60
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:58,840
Yes.

61
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:01,930
Since we don't have everyone here yet,

62
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,440
let's play some mahjong first.

63
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:05,840
Let's sharpen our claws.

64
00:04:08,880 --> 00:04:12,410
To prevent you from saying I tampered with the mahjong machine,

65
00:04:12,440 --> 00:04:13,700
we'll shuffle by hand.

66
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:15,760
Also,

67
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:18,240
we're playing Sichuan mahjong.

68
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,690
No wind or dragon tiles.

69
00:04:20,399 --> 00:04:21,920
Exclude one suit at the start,

70
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:24,250
and exchange three tiles of the same suit.

71
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,600
Four Characters.

72
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:28,040
Kong.

73
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:31,360
Kong again.

74
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,640
And Kong.

75
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:40,000
Winning on a Kong.

76
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:41,120
Good luck.

77
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,440
I've been waiting for you.

78
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:47,800
Luxury Seven Pairs, Full Flush.

79
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:49,520
Pay up.

80
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:54,200
Wait a minute.

81
00:04:54,640 --> 00:04:55,520
Heavenly Hand.

82
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:56,400
All one suit.

83
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:03,560
Officer Shao, your luck is really good today.

84
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:05,160
You keep winning.

85
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:07,040
I've told you many times.

86
00:05:07,040 --> 00:05:08,560
I'm not a cop anymore.

87
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:10,220
Stop calling me Officer Shao.

88
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,520
Also, let me tell you.

89
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:15,080
My luck has always been good.

90
00:05:16,120 --> 00:05:18,560
I'd say you're right not to be a cop.

91
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:20,800
Doing what we do is great.

92
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:21,860
It's interesting.

93
00:05:23,160 --> 00:05:24,240
You're right.

94
00:05:25,160 --> 00:05:27,620
But if I had joined your line of work earlier,

95
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,760
wouldn't you have starved to death?

96
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:32,960
See this?

97
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,400
My teeth are perfectly fine.

98
00:05:35,960 --> 00:05:37,560
Things others can't stomach,

99
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:39,520
I can usually chew them up.

100
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:42,120
Aren't you afraid of getting an upset stomach?

101
00:05:42,720 --> 00:05:45,440
Feeling unwell is better than starving, right?

102
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:47,280
Starving won't kill you.

103
00:05:47,280 --> 00:05:49,560
But stomach problems might.

104
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:50,880
My life is worthless.

105
00:05:51,159 --> 00:05:52,240
As for you, Officer Shao,

106
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:54,280
you should think more about yourself.

107
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,210
One little bird.

108
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,560
Mahjong.

109
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:57,320
Wait.

110
00:05:59,200 --> 00:06:00,880
Me too.

111
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:01,520
Wait.

112
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:03,560
One bird tile.

113
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:04,420
I need that too.

114
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:09,760
Alright, my one bird

115
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:10,640
caused a triple win.

116
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:12,880
Wishing you all a fortune.

117
00:06:15,840 --> 00:06:16,680
Brother Hui.

118
00:06:16,680 --> 00:06:19,080
Fourth Brother and Fifth Brother are here.

119
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:22,240
Good timing, I've lost everything anyway.

120
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:23,960
But all the big shots are here.

121
00:06:24,920 --> 00:06:26,180
Let's get to the table.

122
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,880
We'll play Blackjack.

123
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,600
One deck per round.

124
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:32,540
A new deck every round.

125
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:34,120
To be fair,

126
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,970
all cards will be shuffled by the machine.

127
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,320
We'll rotate the dealer.

128
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:41,720
Starting with the first person clockwise.

129
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,720
Being the dealer or a player is up to you.

130
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:44,850
When it's your turn,

131
00:06:45,280 --> 00:06:47,010
you can refuse to be the dealer.

132
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:08,680
The dealer gets one face-up card and one face-down card.

133
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:10,540
The others get two face-up cards.

134
00:07:11,520 --> 00:07:12,720
Cards 2 through 9

135
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:14,440
are counted at face value.

136
00:07:15,520 --> 00:07:17,680
K, Q, J, and 10

137
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,600
are all counted as 10 points.

138
00:07:19,720 --> 00:07:21,520
An Ace can be counted as 1 point

139
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,120
or 11 points.

140
00:07:23,960 --> 00:07:26,000
There is no five-card limit.

141
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,410
You can keep hitting

142
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,600
until you bust

143
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:31,280
and lose.

144
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,560
20.

145
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:43,120
Stand.

146
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:45,480
Everyone has finished drawing.

147
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:47,840
The dealer must also reveal their hole card.

148
00:07:47,840 --> 00:07:50,600
Everyone compares their hands with the dealer's.

149
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:52,120
If your hand is lower than the dealer's,

150
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:53,050
the dealer wins.

151
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:54,080
If it's a tie,

152
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:55,440
the dealer also wins.

153
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,960
Bet a little more.

154
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,160
Such good luck.

155
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,120
Thank you.

156
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,560
Here comes the luck.

157
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:05,560
Damn.

158
00:08:29,880 --> 00:08:30,920
Sorry about that.

159
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:32,840
20 takes all.

160
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:33,799
Thank you.

161
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,919
Sorry, 21 again.

162
00:08:42,159 --> 00:08:42,720
Hui,

163
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:43,840
you took it all.

164
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,720
I didn't take your chips.

165
00:08:50,800 --> 00:08:52,680
It's 20 points.

166
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:22,160
So big.

167
00:09:22,160 --> 00:09:23,320
Hui,

168
00:09:23,320 --> 00:09:25,360
did you bust already?

169
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,160
What do you think?

170
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:35,800
Sorry.

171
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:38,080
20 points.

172
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:39,080
Takes all.

173
00:10:08,400 --> 00:10:09,760
Your hand is pretty good.

174
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,620
I guess the dealer can't beat you.

175
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,000
Sorry about that.

176
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,880
20 points takes all.

177
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:42,000
Thank you, everyone.

178
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:50,440
Even if I draw, I lose.

179
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,720
You must be cheating.

180
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:53,560
Zhang.

181
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:54,880
Don't get mad.

182
00:10:54,880 --> 00:10:56,160
It's just a game.

183
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,690
You win some, you lose some.

184
00:10:58,120 --> 00:11:00,000
You won so much at mahjong just now.

185
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,280
I didn't say anything.

186
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:03,480
With so many people at the table,

187
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:04,680
you're not the only one losing.

188
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,160
I'm not the only one who won.

189
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:07,440
You say I'm cheating.

190
00:11:07,680 --> 00:11:09,720
That's not very appropriate, is it?

191
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:12,920
If you didn't cheat, you wouldn't keep winning.

192
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,800
I've been here so many times.

193
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:17,360
No matter how much you lose at first,

194
00:11:18,200 --> 00:11:19,600
you never lose in the end.

195
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:21,820
I've lost seven or eight million.

196
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:24,000
We run a casino here,

197
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:26,540
and reputation is what we value the most.

198
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:28,180
If you talk to me like this,

199
00:11:29,520 --> 00:11:30,680
how am I supposed to do business?

200
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:32,080
I don't care about that.

201
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,600
Give me back the money you scammed from me.

202
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:37,080
Or else I'll go out and call the police.

203
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:38,080
All right.

204
00:11:38,080 --> 00:11:39,210
Return everything.

205
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:40,380
Give it back to him.

206
00:11:42,480 --> 00:11:43,540
What are you doing?

207
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:51,560
Hui, I was wrong.

208
00:11:51,560 --> 00:11:52,800
Hui, spare me.

209
00:11:52,800 --> 00:11:53,360
Hui.

210
00:11:57,640 --> 00:11:59,360
Hui, please spare me.

211
00:11:59,840 --> 00:12:01,640
I was talking nonsense just now.

212
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:04,040
I really can't live on.

213
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:06,380
I've lost seven or eight million.

214
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:08,280
My house is mortgaged,

215
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,800
and my family is broken up now.

216
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:11,980
Please have mercy.

217
00:12:12,400 --> 00:12:13,330
Be a good person,

218
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,840
and give me some back.

219
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:16,840
I am a good person.

220
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:18,160
I heard your family is broken up.

221
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:18,800
You lost your house,

222
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:20,260
and you lost 7 or 8 million.

223
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:21,770
Is one thousand enough?

224
00:13:00,960 --> 00:13:01,960
Again.

225
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,600
Okay.

226
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:04,980
How about this.

227
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:07,400
This round, you go 1v1 against me.

228
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:09,680
Even if it's a tie,

229
00:13:09,680 --> 00:13:11,140
it counts as my loss, okay?

230
00:13:11,760 --> 00:13:12,520
Come on.

231
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:14,880
I'll play with you.

232
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:15,400
Deal.

233
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,520
This round, I have 16 points.

234
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:29,440
I pass.

235
00:13:30,040 --> 00:13:31,440
Giving you a chance, bro.

236
00:13:35,440 --> 00:13:36,240
Come on.

237
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:48,200
Rub it hard.

238
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:14,520
I'm really sorry, everyone,

239
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,080
for this little episode.

240
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,880
But it's not my fault.

241
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:19,960
You can beat me or scold me.

242
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:21,010
That's fine.

243
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,570
But you can't insult me.

244
00:14:22,840 --> 00:14:25,400
I absolutely cannot tolerate being accused of cheating.

245
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:26,960
I'm a man of my word.

246
00:14:27,240 --> 00:14:28,440
Shall we continue?

247
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:36,580
I've lost almost all my money.

248
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,200
I'll take off now.

249
00:14:39,240 --> 00:14:40,320
Good luck making a fortune, everyone.

250
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:41,650
Midnight snack is on me.

251
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:43,040
Come again, bro.

252
00:14:43,040 --> 00:14:43,720
Come again.

253
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:44,200
I won't see you out.

254
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,000
Come again.

255
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:48,720
Gentlemen.

256
00:14:49,240 --> 00:14:50,700
I'm good. Let's continue.

257
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:51,930
Let's continue.

258
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:53,920
I can also continue,

259
00:14:55,080 --> 00:14:55,880
but

260
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,780
I have two conditions.

261
00:14:59,600 --> 00:15:00,400
First,

262
00:15:01,680 --> 00:15:03,520
blackjack is really too boring.

263
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:05,050
Let's play something else.

264
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:06,880
Let's play Showhand.

265
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,140
Second condition,

266
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:13,200
I want to play you one-on-one

267
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,770
because I don't trust them.

268
00:15:20,840 --> 00:15:21,640
Officer Shao,

269
00:15:22,160 --> 00:15:23,490
what do you mean by that?

270
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:25,360
Are you saying

271
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,840
that these two are my shills

272
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:28,370
and we're putting on an act?

273
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:30,240
What I just said

274
00:15:30,240 --> 00:15:31,360
and what just happened,

275
00:15:31,360 --> 00:15:32,440
have you completely forgotten?

276
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:33,440
I haven't forgotten.

277
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,600
Then what do you mean?

278
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:37,400
My money didn't grow on trees either.

279
00:16:01,920 --> 00:16:02,450
Brother.

280
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,020
How about this.

281
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:04,880
You two.

282
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,560
Officer Shao

283
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,240
is in high spirits today.

284
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:10,040
We'll play alone for a while.

285
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:11,680
Let's play another day.

286
00:16:11,680 --> 00:16:13,400
Sorry about this.

287
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:18,640
Come on.

288
00:16:19,720 --> 00:16:20,240
Come on.

289
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:33,880
A Queen.

290
00:17:41,640 --> 00:17:42,370
Brother Hui.

291
00:17:42,680 --> 00:17:43,940
